      "content": "that feels a bit harsh tbh. a lot of these local shops are the backbone of the community, and saying they'll just be \"left behind\" because they can't afford expensive new tech sounds a bit extreme. isn't there a risk that these regs actually kill off competition and favor big corporations who can easily afford the compliance, while the little guys just go under?",
